<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,457,403,429]" box="[189,457,403,429]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,457,403,429]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,457,403,429]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[189,1399,450,617]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
A mostly bright yellow species with hyaline wings, otherwise characterized by the combination of the punctate clypeus, the concave and flanged subtegular ridge, and the sharp mid-longitudinal carina on the frons, which separates this species from other yellow species with hyaline wings (these species have a strigose or hardly sculptured clypeus, and all of them except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1951" box="[892,1018,555,581]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Epirhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uelensis">
<emphasis box="[892,1018,555,581]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">E. uelensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have no flange on the subtegular ridge).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
